Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new approach to facilitate the design of modular port graph models for complex systems, which is a software engineering problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper mentions an example of application in functional programming. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with graph transformation systems and rewriting rules. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is possible as the paper mentions the use of attributes to store user-defined data, which is a common technique in AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper mentions an example of application in financial modelling, which can be seen as a control system.
